commit cc12d9e6a6bd4782c2584f244aaf095de55a4926
Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 24 15:44:44 2026 -0500

    fix(security/cargo): rename pyo3 *_bound APIs to drop deprecation warnings (clippy -D warnings)
    
    - Python::get_type_bound -> Python::get_type (19 call sites)
    - PyErr::value_bound -> PyErr::value (5 call sites)
    Both are pure renames; no signature changes, no behavior changes.
    pyo3 0.24.1 deprecated the _bound suffixes; 0.28.x removes them
    entirely. This unblocks clippy -D warnings on the 0.24.1 bump that
    closed RUSTSEC-2025-0020.
    
    Verifications: clippy exit 0, fathomdb-py 4/4, fathomdb-napi 4/4,
    agent-verify 0 new blockers (AC-037 sandbox pre-existing).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

